               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">F. C. KITCHEN</hi> (<hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi>) The ten tons of goods that I sold were lying at Manchester, they were to be delivered to Brown &amp; Rintoul's order and they thought they were in Liverpool—there was a contract for the sale which was handed to Cooper—that was sent on the 6th December and the invoice was sent on the 31st—I had refused to credit Brown &amp; Rintoul—we would not give them credit—I had no conversation with Cooper on the subject.</p>
